                            <comment id="14247732" author="jahewson" created="Tue, 16 Dec 2014 04:29:50 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s two thing happening here, the first is that the mutually recursive isSymbolic() call inside isStandard14() appears to be unnecessary. I&apos;ve removed it and tested with the files from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2372&quot; title=&quot;Trash Glyphs: Regressions 19.9.2014&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;PDFBOX-2372&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;PDFBOX-2372&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and did not see any problems.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The second is that Adobe Acrobat is treating &quot;Times,Bold&quot; as a standard 14 name, which isn&apos;t even documented in Adobe&apos;s 32000 supplement. Here&apos;s a screenshot from Acrobat Pro IX&apos;s Preflight:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;image-wrap&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/12687398/12687398_preflight.png&quot; style=&quot;border: 0px solid black&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
